From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000001 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Developer <dev@example.com>
Date: Wed, 01 Apr 2026 00:48:21 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 1/1] drm/xe: add Xe native context for virglrenderer

Implements the host-side virglrenderer native context for the Intel Xe
GPU driver (xe.ko).  Guest userspace (ANV under virtio-gpu) communicates
with the host through the xe_virtio ccmd protocol defined in xe_proto.h.

New files added under src/drm/xe/:
  xe_proto.h           - shared guest/host wire protocol structs
  xe_ccmd.h / .c       - handlers for all 8 protocol commands
  xe_object.h / .c     - GEM object wrapper (cpu_caching -> map_info)
  xe_resource.h / .c   - virgl blob / attach / export helpers
  xe_renderer.h / .c   - context probe / create / destroy / submit_fence
  ../drm-uapi/xe_drm.h - vendored Xe kernel uAPI header

Protocol commands implemented:
  XE_CCMD_DEVICE_QUERY        proxy for DRM_IOCTL_XE_DEVICE_QUERY (2-phase)
  XE_CCMD_GEM_CREATE          create GEM BO linked to a virgl blob
  XE_CCMD_VM_CREATE           create Xe VM; host returns vm_id
  XE_CCMD_VM_DESTROY          destroy Xe VM
  XE_CCMD_VM_BIND             synchronous VM bind (res_id -> gem handle)
  XE_CCMD_EXEC_QUEUE_CREATE   create exec queue + per-queue drm_timeline
  XE_CCMD_EXEC_QUEUE_DESTROY  drain timeline and destroy exec queue
  XE_CCMD_EXEC                submit batch; host syncobj feeds drm_timeline

Design notes:
  - VM bind is always synchronous; ordering is guaranteed by the ccmd seqno.
  - EXEC creates a temporary DRM syncobj as out-sync, calls XE_EXEC, then
    exports the sync-fd into the per-queue drm_timeline for virgl fences.
  - Exec queues are tracked in a u32 -> drm_timeline* hash table.
  - submit_fence() uses exec_queue_id directly as the ring_idx.
  - Enable with meson option: -Ddrm-renderers=xe-experimental

Signed-off-by: Developer <dev@example.com>
